<HEADLINE>
<P>
SOCIETY SECURITY EARNINGS CAP 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Your editorial advocating the elimination of the Social Security "earnings cap" 
was right on the mark ("Time to Eliminate the Inequity," Jan. 7). It is high 
time that our nation recognizes the value of our seniors and stops this 
counterproductive practice. 
</P>
<P>
I have introduced a bill in Congress (HR 311) that will do just as your 
editorial recommended -- remove the earnings limitation altogether. The 
earnings test places an unfair penalty on the elderly. I hold by the philosophy 
that "a dollar earned is a dollar earned" and I can see no justification for 
requiring a forfeiture of $1 in Social Security benefits for every $2 or $3 
earned. 
</P>
<P>
Specifically, I believe we should allow senior citizens to maintain full and 
productive lives and to earn their full value for any work. These are the 
people who possess knowledge and experience that are invaluable to our economy. 
</P>
<P>
REP. RON PACKARD 
</P>
<P>
R-Carlsbad 
</P>
</TEXT>
