<HEADLINE>
<P>
'CHANGES IN HEALTH CARE' 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
I am a hemodialysis patient who depends on dialysis three times a week to 
survive. 
</P>
<P>
Medicare has informed us who dialyze at home that Congress has cut costs by 50% 
on Method II dialysis which will affect many dialysis patients like myself. 
This will mean going back to a unit where the care is not as good as what you 
receive at home. What upsets me is reading in the paper where President Bush 
has approved salary increases of up to 35% for top government workers and yet 
has done nothing to solve this Medicare crisis. All I can say is where is the 
justice by doing this? 
</P>
<P>
DEBORAH CARRILLO 
</P>
<P>
Lakewood 
