<BYLINE>
<P>
From Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Brian MacLellan scored four goals and Sergei Makarov scored the winner with 
eight minutes remaining to give the Calgary Flames a 6-5 victory Sunday night 
at Chicago. 
</P>
<P>
MacLellan, who had only three goals in 33 previous games, scored the game's 
first three goals. 
</P>
<P>
He had his fifth career hat trick and his second four-goal game. 
</P>
<P>
Steve Thomas scored three times for Chicago, which had its six-game unbeaten 
string end. Thomas and Steve Larmer scored 64 seconds apart in the third 
period, making the score 5-5 at 3:34. 
</P>
<P>
Winnipeg 6, St. Louis 5 -- Dave McLlwain scored two goals and set up Paul 
Fenton's game-winner with 2:04 remaining at Winnipeg. 
</P>
<P>
The Jets won despite three goals by Brett Hull, who has a league-leading total 
of 41 goals in 45 games. 
</P>
<P>
It was Winnipeg's fourth consecutive victory and increased the Jets' unbeaten 
streak at home to eight games. 
</P>
<P>
New York Rangers 4, Philadelphia 3 -- Brian Leetch scored at 1:16 of overtime 
to give the Rangers their 1,000th home victory. 
</P>
<P>
Leetch's shot through a screen from the left point beat Ken Wregget and capped 
a three-goal Ranger comeback. It was the first time in 18 games that the 
Rangers won after trailing in the third period. They had been 0-15-2. 
</P>
