<HEADLINE>
<P>
NEWSWIRE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Yugoslavia's Veronika Sarec, who last week failed to finish in two races, 
gained her first World Cup victory in the women's slalom at Haus Im Ennstal, 
Austria. 
</P>
<P>
Sarec had a time of 1 minute 31.22 seconds for the two runs. 
</P>
<P>
The surprise of the second run was the failure of Switzerland's Vreni Schneider 
to finish. 
</P>
<P>
Schneider fell for the first time since she tumbled in a race in Piancavallo, 
Italy, in December, 1987. 
</P>
