<TEXT>
<P>
Uwe-Jens Mey, the East German gold medalist at the 1988 Olympics, and Norway's 
Johann Olav Koss won the windup events in a two-day World Cup speed-skating 
event at Davos, Switzerland. 
</P>
<P>
Mey won the 1,000 meters in 1 minute 14.41 seconds, .85 seconds better than Uwe 
Steeb of West Germany. Koss won the 5,000 meters in 6:51.38. 
</P>
