<P>
TRADING EAST: With the Iron Curtain down, Western companies want to figure out 
how to trade profitably with the East Bloc (D4). . . . The key question, says 
Jim Harrell of Intertrade in Laguna Niguel: "What does a country do that does 
not have currency, but needs things that take hard currency to buy?" . . . 
Harrell has negotiated complex deals involving Poland, Romania, the Soviet 
Union, China and Cambodia. . . . In one, U.S. medical gear was sent to the 
Soviet Union for raw cotton, which was milled in Mexico and sent to China, 
where it was turned into K mart sweat shirts. Mark I. Pinsky and Steve Emmons 
</P>
