<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: LOS ALAMITOS; 
</P>
<P>
COUNCIL OKS HIGHER PARKING PENALTIES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Parking illegally in Los Alamitos became more expensive this week when the City 
Council approved sharp increases in fines for the most common violations. 
</P>
<P>
Red-curb and 72-hour parking violations will increase from $19 to $32, and 
parking in a fire lane will now cost $54 instead of $29. 
</P>
<P>
Most other violations, including parking in front of a fire hydrant, parking 
too far from the curb, parking on a sidewalk or in a crosswalk, and parking 
within 15 feet of a public driveway, will now cost $32, up from $29. 
</P>
<P>
Police Chief James Guess said a random survey of six other Orange County cities 
showed that Los Alamitos had been charging from 10% to 105% less for these 
violations than the other cities. For instance, a fire lane violation in Los 
Alamitos cost $29, while in Anaheim, Buena Park and Tustin it is $56. 
</P>
<P>
The rates were last increased two years ago, Guess said. The rate increase 
approved by the council Monday goes into effect immediately. 
</P>
</TEXT>
