<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: SEAL BEACH; 
</P>
<P>
863 WERE RESCUED BY LIFEGUARDS IN '89 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MICHELLE NICOLOSI 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Lifeguards rescued 863 people and prevented more than 70,000 potential 
incidents on the city's beach last year, according to a report by lifeguard 
chief Tim Dorsey. 
</P>
<P>
Superb weather brought large crowds to the beach, Dorsey wrote, resulting in a 
dramatic increase in lifesaving work. In 1988, the lifeguards rescued about 650 
swimmers. 
</P>
<P>
In addition to the rescues, lifeguards administered major first aid to nine 
people and minor first aid to about 800 people in 1989, the report said. No 
drownings were reported. MICHELLE NICOLOSI 
</P>
</TEXT>
