<HEADLINE>
<P>
GOFF'S JERSEY NUMBER TO BE RETIRED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By TOM HAMILTON 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Former Magnolia High School basketball forward Mike Goff, who died on Dec. 16, 
will have his jersey number, 30, retired during pregame ceremonies Jan. 26 at 
the school's gymnasium. 
</P>
<P>
Goff was the county's leading scorer and rebounder in the 1987-88 season, 
averaging 28.2 points and 16.7 rebounds. Goff was playing for Fullerton College 
when he died at his family's home. He was 19. TOM HAMILTON 
</P>
</TEXT>
