GM to Build Cars in Hungary: General Motors Corp. formally announced that it 
has reached a tentative agreement with Hungarian government-owned auto maker 
RABA to jointly build cars and engines at a plant under construction in 
Szentgotthard, near the Austrian border, beginning in 1992. The deal makes GM 
the first U.S. auto maker to invest in Eastern Europe. GM spokesman R. L. 
Theis, said the company will invest $150 million. 
</P>
