10-day space journey. After releasing one satellite and rescuing another last 
week, the crew of five turned to the mission's secondary goals -- several 
scientific and medical experiments. G. David Low performed a test on himself, 
left, to gather data on cardiovascular response during flight. This journey -- 
the second-longest in 33 shuttle missions -- is intended as a stepping stone 
toward months-long stints aboard the space station Freedom. Associated Press 
</P>
