<HEADLINE>
<P>
POLICE HAVE NO LEADS IN SLASHING OF ACTRESS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
NEW YORK 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Police on Sunday said they had no clues to knife attacks on two pedestrians in 
Manhattan, one of whom was actress Viveca Lindfors. 
</P>
<P>
The Swedish-born Lindfors, 69, suffered a facial wound that took 28 stitches 
but said she would not be intimidated by gangs. Dennis Beal, 36, of New York 
was slashed just a few minutes earlier Saturday morning and within 3 blocks of 
the spot in Greenwich Village where Lindfors was attacked. Beal suffered cuts 
on his face that required 40 stitches. 
</P>
<P>
Police said they believed that a few marauding youths were responsible for the 
two slashings, but they drew a blank as to their identities. 
</P>
