1ST INDEPENDENT PAPER SET UP IN E. GERMANY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Reuters 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
EAST BERLIN 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
East German journalists have taken over a regional Communist daily and are 
turning it into the country's first independent newspaper, one of its editors 
said Sunday. 
</P>
<P>
Peter Sterzing said the editorial staff and printing workers agreed to make the 
newspaper, Das Volk, into a daily free of links with any parties. 
</P>
<P>
"It will in future appear as the Thueringer Allgemeine and will be run by an 
editorial council elected by secret ballot," he said. 
</P>
<P>
The newspaper, based in the southern regional city of Erfurt, has a circulation 
of 400,000. 
