</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Florida forward Livingston Chatman has decided to leave the basketball team for 
an indefinite period. The 6-foot-7 junior from Lakeland, Fla., cited an injured 
knee and burnout as reasons for leaving the team. 
</P>
<P>
Chatman did not attend Florida's 84-62 win over Auburn Saturday in Gainesville 
after it was announced he would not play because of a sore knee and an ankle 
injury sustained in Wednesday's loss at Kentucky. 
