<HEADLINE>
<P>
LOCAL; 
</P>
<P>
MAN STEPS IN FRONT OF CAR, KILLED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Service Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Los Angeles police this morning identified a man killed when he stepped in 
front of a car on a Studio City street as a transient who had previously been 
cited for jaywalking in the area. 
</P>
<P>
John William Kocan, 46, was killed about 7 p.m. Sunday when he walked out into 
traffic on Coldwater Canyon Avenue near Dickens Street and was struck by a 
northbound car, Detective Don Bellante said. 
</P>
<P>
Police declined to identify the driver of the car because he was not cited in 
the accident. 
</P>
<P>
"It was not the driver's fault," Bellante said. "This guy wandered out into the 
street where there was no crosswalk and into the traffic. He had done this 
before." 
</P>
<P>
The detective said results of tests to determine if Kocan was intoxicated when 
struck by the car Sunday were not completed. 
</P>
</TEXT>
