<P>
TAIWAN MARKET HITS NEW HIGH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
TAIPEI, Taiwan 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Taiwan's irrepressible stock market bounded to a record high today, living up 
to its reputation for astronomical gains by rising 12.9% in the first two weeks 
of 1990 alone. 
</P>
<P>
Taipei brokerage houses were crowded with excited small investors, as mothers 
with babies, taxi drivers on break and elderly couples all craned for a glimpse 
of the rising numbers on the computer stock board. 
</P>
<P>
"Last week I was a bit nervous, but not anymore," said Ann Lin, a well-dressed 
young office worker. 
</P>
<P>
The index shot up 308.44 points to end at 10,867.64 -- a stunning 1,243.46 
point gain over the market's 9,624.18 opening on Jan. 4, the first trading day 
of the year. 
</P>
<P>
The previous record was 10,773.11 on Sept. 25. 
</P>
</TEXT>
