P. M. BRIEFING; 
</P>
<P>
EC JOBLESS RATE HITS 7-YEAR LOW 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
LUXEMBOURG 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The European Community's unemployment rate fell to a seven-year low of 8.9% 
during November, EC's statistics agency Eurostat announced today. 
</P>
<P>
The decline in November -- from 9% in October and 9.7% in November, 1988 -- put 
the jobless rate below 9% for the first time since 1982. 
</P>
<P>
Henning Christophersen, the EC's economic affairs commissioner, said the drop 
showed the investment and growth-oriented policies of the 12-nation trading 
bloc were working. 
</P>
<P>
Eurostat said national unemployment rates either fell slightly or were 
unchanged in November except in West Germany and Denmark. The rise in West 
Germany reflected the movement of East German workers to the West seeking jobs, 
the statement said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
